### Project ignores
tmp/
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock
.claude/worktrees/
.codex
.idea/
.playwright-mcp/

### Python toolchain artifacts (per Phase 1 sub-step 12)
# Note: .mypy_cache/ is intentionally NOT listed. Mypy
# compatibility is a python-skill-script-style-requirements.md
# non-goal (livespec uses pyright); its cache path is therefore
# not a tolerated artifact. If .mypy_cache/ appears, something
# unexpected ran mypy and that should be investigated rather
# than ignored.
__pycache__/
.pytest_cache/
.hypothesis/
.coverage
.coverage.*
.ruff_cache/
.pyright/
.mutmut-cache/
mutants/
htmlcov/

### UV / lefthook local state
.venv/

### Beads / Dolt
# Per-clone bd state (Dolt working copy, lockfiles, runtime artifacts)
# is excluded by .beads/.gitignore (bd-managed, tracked itself). The
# only top-level entry is the credential key, which is global rather
# than per-project.
.beads-credential-key
# NOTE: `.beads/config.yaml` is now TRACKED (epic li-ws2iv4 cutover to
# the per-repo livespec-orchestrator-beads-fabro Dolt tenant). The committed config
# carries the server-mode connection block with NO per-machine
# project_id and NO password (the tenant password is supplied via the
# BEADS_DOLT_PASSWORD env var at bd-call time). Per-clone bd runtime
# state stays excluded by .beads/.gitignore. The prior per-machine
# remote-URL thrash rationale no longer applies under server mode.

